UNITED STATES of America v. Leona B. FROST, in Her Own Name and as Administratrix, etc. No. 9341. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 30, 1939. Frank E. Flynn, U. S. Atty., of Phoenix, Ariz. Harry O. Juliani, of Tucson, Ariz., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties for dismissal of the appeal herein, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
